\begin_layout Standard
\align left

\family typewriter
sysconfig.local.inc.php
\family default
 is a file that does the same configuration as 
\family typewriter
sysconfig.inc.php
\family default
.
 However, for local changes, it's recommended to just change the file 
\family typewriter
sysconfig.local.inc.php
\family default
 .
 Logically, if there are two common configurations in the two files, SLiMS
 will read 
\family typewriter
sysconfig.local.inc.php
\family default
 as overriding 
\family typewriter
sysconfig.inc.php
\family default
 .
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For example:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align left
If, in the file 
\family typewriter
sysconfig.inc.php
\family default
 there is a line: 
\family typewriter
$sysconf['ucs']['enable'] = false;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align left
And in the file
\family typewriter
 sysconfig.local.inc.php
\family default
 there is a line: 
\family typewriter
$sysconf['ucs']['enable'] = true;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then the SLiMS application will use the configuration of the value as =
 true.
\end_layout

