\begin_layout Section
Enabling Apache and MySQL in psenayan as an automatic service in Microsoft
 Windows
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Apache web server and MySQL database in a portable Senayan used on Microsoft
 Windows operating systems, can be run automatically, without having to
 turn on 
\family typewriter
mysql_start.bat
\family default
 and 
\family typewriter
apache_start.bat
\family default
 file manually.
 This is done by making the two files into services.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
vskip 1em
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We start by opening a command prompt in Windows.
 To install the Apache web server as a service, make sure that we are already
 in the directory psenayan.
 ( cd to the psenayan directory).
 Enter the command:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code

\backslash
psenayan
\backslash
apache
\backslash
bin
\backslash
httpd.exe -k install -n Apache2.2
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For example, if we put psenayan on drive D:, then the command is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
D:
\backslash
psenayan
\backslash
apache
\backslash
bin> httpd.exe -k install -n Apache2.2 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The above command makes the Apache web server run automatically when Windows
 starts up.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
vskip 1em
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After the Apache web server, the next step is to set the MySQL database
 as a service in a portable Senayan system.
 Just like the previous process, first make sure we are in the directory
 psenayan.
 ( cd to the psenayan directory) .
 Enter the command:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
<directory name>>:
\backslash
psenayan
\backslash
mysql
\backslash
bin
\backslash
mysqld.exe –install
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For example, if we put psenayan on drive D:, then the command is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
D:
\backslash
psenayan
\backslash
mysql
\backslash
bin> mysqld.exe --install
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The above commands have enabled MySQL as a service.
 The next step is to change some parts of the 
\family typewriter
my.ini
\family default
 file, located in the directory 
\family typewriter
psenayan
\backslash
mysql
\family default
.
 We have to change the 
\family typewriter
\shape italic
basedir
\family default
\shape default
 and 
\family typewriter
\shape italic
datadir
\family default
\shape default
 there.
 These sections in the 
\family typewriter
my.ini
\family default
 file are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
# set basedir to your installation path 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
basedir=/psenayan/mysql 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
# set datadir to the location of your data directory 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
datadir=/psenayan/mysql/data
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code

\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
What must be changed is the addition of the directory where psenayan's 
\family typewriter
\shape italic
basedir
\family default
\shape default
 and 
\family typewriter
\shape italic
datadir
\family default
\shape default
 are stored.
 Since in our example we put the psenayan directory on drive D:, then the
 form of the changes is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
# set basedir to your installation path 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
basedir=D:/psenayan/mysql 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
# set datadir to the location of your data directory 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
datadir=D:/psenayan/mysql/data
\end_layout

